```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```
This function takes a DateTime object `dt` and an integer `bump` as input. If `bump` is not provided, it defaults to 3. The function then returns a new DateTime object that is `bump` hours later than the input `dt`. If the input is not a DateTime object, the function will throw a MethodError.
